cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of open-set classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves training networks for joint classification and reconstruction of input data, which is a common approach in deep learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the robustness of the method to diverse outliers, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of latent representations for reconstruction is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
